        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>April 16</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have just discovered that at a more distant station viz Chiselhurst on the same line there is a rather later train, viz one leaving at 9<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 34<hi rend="superscript">’</hi>, but Chiselhurst is a full hour’s drive from my house.</p>
<p>If not inconvenient to you &amp; D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Maudsley, will you return by this train, which will give us nearly 1,<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></formula> hour instead of only a full hour. I can send you in my carriage to Chiselhurst Station. So if this suits you, do not keep your Fly from Orpington; but you can take return tickets, as the 2 stations are on the same line.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>In Haste | Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>I am sure you &amp; D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Maudsley will allow me to leave the room for quarter of an hour, if my head fails me.—</p>
<p>The 9<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. 34<hi rend="superscript">’</hi> Train from Chiselhurst reaches Charing Cross at 10<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>, 11<hi rend="superscript">’</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 a more] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘the’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.1 viz Chiselhurst] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.2 Chiselhurst] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">1.3 from my house] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘to it.’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n5">2.00 nearly] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by a reference to the visit of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2912.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Friend Lewin</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3227.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Maudsley</ref> in <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242) for 17 April 1872.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Chislehurst and Orpington were on the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4474.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">South Eastern Railway</ref> line; Chislehurst is about four miles and Orpington eight miles from Down. See also <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8603.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Henry Maudsley, 6 November 1872</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
